cs.LG, cs.STAT, cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.SI 

This paper deals with hyperparameter estimation in kernel-based regularization methods, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.STAT (Statistics). The paper also involves optimization and convergence analysis, which suggests the categories cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the properties of different estimators, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
